name: Are You Experienced
beta: Sit start on the left side, then traverse right across the main face, conserving energy for the final crux. The final crux by itself is a three-star V4 stand start on a left hand sloper meatwrap gaston and a right hand knobby crimp. FA: Russell Bobzien.
Stand start left arete/corner. Or V5 sit start.

name: Manitou
beta: Sit start on left hand side-pull scoop and go up past right hand crimper gaston crux. Mantra Man V11 sit start same as Manitou but go up using the gaston as a crimper under-cling. Manitou Man V11 start Manitou finish Mantra Man. FA: Russell Bobzien.

name: Little Wing
beta: Sit start Mantra Man, go up using the big right hand sloper rail. V7 stand start same as Manitou and Mantra Man. When the sand is low or gone or if you just can't reach the good starting edge, a pad stack or cheat stone is legit.

name: Central Scrutinizer
beta: V5 sit start to direct topout or V4 sit start to right.

name: Standard Route
beta: Stand start on under-cling side-pulls and climb up right into the slabby groove to topout. V3 sit start on left hand horn.

name: Smiley Face
beta: Stand start on right hand crimper edge. V6 sit start on sloper.

name: The Red Monster
beta: Stand or sit start into highball face. Drop off of jugs at lip or topout the V0X slab. Don't forget you'll have to down climb V0X to get off.

name: Ah Baloney
beta: Stand start on obvious jug down and left of arête. Make moves up and right past arête to topout on a slopey ledge. To descend, down climb and jump for the pads between the boulders at the base.

name: The Green Monster
beta: Stand start in the center of the main (southwest) face of The Green Monster and go straight up to a ledge about 15 to 20 ft. above the ground. Climb down and left to #8 to descend. In winter the sand goes down, exposing jagged rocks and making this highball problem even higherball (V3R). The sit start is V4 and V4R in winter.

name: V5
beta: Low sit start on left hand lie-back. Traverse up and right into #6 to finish.

name: V0
beta: Stand start then up face. Topout on ledge then climb back down or traverse off left to nearby rock to descend. V0R Highball in winter when the sand is low.
